The paper proposes a new active learning method based on GANs for generating high entropy samples. This method is applicable to multi-class problems and outperforms random sample selection. The paper involves machine learning, computer vision, natural language processing, and neural networks, which are all covered by the above-mentioned sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
